annotation.TEXT: I also like how I can keep making silly mistakes... Not!
Yay, the launch was a success!
Alright, now let's descend this mountain!
Yeah, I can't move past the flames, because they're just as solid as munchers. Umm... I don't recall Layer 2 screwing up on me here like that before...
And that should be game!
Actually, I feel like doing one more level right now, so let's head Back to Land.
BGM: Yoshi's Cookie (SNES) - Action Theme B - Csikos Post
Yay for pointless shell jumps! But, honestly, the cape does make shell jumping a little easier.
BLOCK FACTORYYY!!!
There's some switch blocks. I forget if red ! blocks contain items in this hack. I don't think they do, but I'm not 100% sure right now.
Mouser? They put you in charge of world 3? Well, this should be a piece of cake...
Ooh! I pulled it off! I managed to break a piece of this wall with a spin jump!
Oh, what?! You all saw that, right? I totally landed on the guy after he fully appeared, and I instead phased right through him without hitting him! I hate that glitch!
MULTI KILL!
And here's midpoint, along with an invisible plot wall that keeps you from going to the left. (Okay, that invisible wall doesn't have anything to do with the plot... or maybe it does...)
Ow! Well, that maneuver was certainly not one of my brightest ideas...
Oops. Well, I already determined that to be a multi-coin block, so it's no big deal.
BGM: Paper Mario (N64) - Shiver Mountain
Well, it's nice to know that I get a spare mushroom, just before it's boss time!
Oh, you know what? I bet it's because I moved to the right during this small transition room here, and that screwed up Layer 2 in the next room for some reason.
The lag made that Mega Mole kill more epic than it had any right to be!
In T minus 3...

Yeah, and now that the flames are in the correct spots and not blocking my view as much, I get through this area flawlessly. (Well, it probably also helped that I had just played through this room a couple minutes ago too.)
Ah, here is what I obviously need to bring back to the previous room.
To be continued... (Ooh, the next level might require me to stay over 50 MPH!)
Yeah, now the afterburners look properly aligned. Well, I won't blame this hack's creator for that glitch, because it was totally unexpected.
D'oh! How'd I screw that up?
Argh! I totally didn't see that ambush coming...
We have liftoff!
I'll just speed through this bonus game here...
Okay, this is definitely an unfair glitch, so I'm going to do some rewinding here. This will not add to the demo counter.
DOUBLE KILL!
However, this upside-down pipe where the screen stops scrolling is certainly worth checking! ...If I could get into it... What the heck? Why are the flames out of position like this?
Alright, I get my flower back here. Now let's try to avoid having any more injuries for a while.
Uh, oh. I'm not entirely loyal to his Fierceness. Maybe I should leave.
Too bad I can't leave because there's no side exit here. Besides, I don't really want to leave anyway!
Yeah, it's a trap. Bowser's trying to make me BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! WOO! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN!
Now, do I glitch the P-switch into the next room, or do I just take the springboard with me? Hmm...
Oh, come on... Why am I having trouble with this stupid Geruta?
Well, I know how to stop this shell attack... (Of course, I could've just fried them, too.)
Oh, cool. I like how the koopas are all dressed for this cold weather.
Huh. So, just the multi-coin block, and that single coin down there, and that's all there is of interest in those blocks. I was hoping for a power up of some sort.
Okay, midpoint will repair one of my hits, and then I can get another power up here. And, with a successful block clone, I can get yet another power up! Nice!
At least there's a replacement power up right here, although it's no cape.
Well, that answers my previous question from before. The red ! blocks do not hold items.
Alright, you are cleared for liftoff...
Okay, well, I was going to carry this springboard across the finish line for a free life, but now I'm just going to carry it across for a replacement flower instead.
No, I am not going to check that upside-down pipe up there. Even I'm not that insane. (If that pipe does lead somewhere, let me know!)
Whoa, I'm having a number of close calls here.
And now we're in Bob-omb territory it seems.
Demo count: SR388
That was neat. I wasn't expecting that bullet to be there when I thwacked the koopa.
LOL!
BGM: SMB3 - Airship
I also like it when I spin jump on a Dry Bones while caped and bounce off of it while simultaneously killing it like that.
Yeah, and with that, my lives are maxed out!
Another invisible teleport wall...
Ouch! Man, it's tricky to avoid everything here, especially with those afterburners obscuring my view.
Gotta check every turn block before Magikoopa gets to them...
Well, that sucked... Too bad JUSTIN BAILEY doesn't make you indestructible like the NARPAS SWORD does...
And that's game! Wait, I have to get rid of all lingering Bob-ombs, and then that's game!
And now that this pipe is properly unblocked, I can proceed like normal.
BGM: Madness Fortress
Huh. That's interesting how I was able to cape spin that bullet from there, even though it looked like it was too low.
Whoa! Man, I've gotta stay alert for those surprise attacks!
Oh, cool. I like this castle/fortress music.
Honestly, is this the best time for me to be checking every pipe?
Nothing up there, so let's go to the right where a wall of invisible teleport blocks will take me to an autoscrolling area.
So, what other stuff awaits me in world 4? Find out next time!
Oh, that's neat.
Well, I definitely made the right choice in bringing the springboard. Otherwise, I would've had a hard time getting that Yoshi coin!
Uh, oh... Danger music!
Ooh, but at least I can get my cape back here!
BGM: Final Fantasy IV - Boss Battle
Yay, I get my cape back. Now, what's down this pipe?
Now, let's have no stupid mistakes on this Chuck, okay?
This is the NES Metroid, obviously.
BARF! And even in front of the goal, I make a stupid mistake!
BGM: Donkey Kong Country 2 - Run, Rambi! Run!
Well, since it's asking me nicely for the pass word...
Oh, man. I wonder if I'll need this P-switch to simply stay alive at some point up ahead...
Of course, Thwimp's in the wrong sprite slot to get hit... And, I've taken out Cheatikoopa, so now I have to wait for him to respawn... unless, maybe I can...
Oh, that's funny. Three times in a row, I kicked a Bob-omb during the frame of animation where it turned white!
Oh, come on! I'm letting this guy murder me here!
Anything up here? Just curious.
And yes, you want to put in all dashes on the second row.

What? You're still alive? Oh, this must be the 5 HP variety of Mouser. Okay, then I guess your world 3 position makes more sense. However, shouldn't you have a Spark (or Lil Sparky) going around the perimeter of your room as well?
There's another upside-down pipe that I'm not going to check.
I think I'll take the springboard. It'll probably be more useful.
MEGA KILL!
Okay, that's enough fooling around here.
However, I believe that glitch could be fixed by simply disabling horizontal scrolling in the small transition room just before this room.
Ha! Nice try there, koopa!
I may no longer have a cape, but I can totally get that 1-up that I don't really need.
Looks like this'll be a puzzle of some sort.
Find out next time!
And here's where you can use the P-switch, where you get rewarded with a 1-up. However, if you miss the P-switch, you aren't forced to die. This hack isn't that mean.
Alright, now up next is the last level of world 3, Sky Castle. Let's hope I won't stumble upon another game-breaking glitch here...
Hello, and welcome back to more rampagin'! Now, let's take a look at the votes to determine which order I'll be doing the last two levels of world 3...
And that's about it for this level. Is there anything to the right of the goal sphere? Nope, doesn't look like there's anything I care about.
Yep, as I thought, this pipe is 2-way.
Yep, Sky Secret 2 won, so let's do this thing!

This password starts you in upper Norfair as armor-less Samus (which doesn't actually affect your defense), with 5 energy tanks, 255 missiles, the Screw Attack, the Varia Suit, the High Jump Boots, and the Wave Beam.
